{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T17:23:08.362Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Chain of Thought (CoT) prompting comes in "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"three main approaches"},{"type":"text","text":" that differ in how much guidance you provide: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Basic CoT"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Guided CoT"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured CoT"},{"type":"text","text":". Each has different strengths and use cases, from simple \"think step by step\" prompts to rigorously constrained reasoning templates."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Basic CoT (Zero-Shot & Few-Shot)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Basic CoT"},{"type":"text","text":" is the simplest form—just asking the model to show its reasoning steps without imposing strict templates or external structure."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Types of Basic CoT"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"A. Zero-Shot Basic CoT"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Just add "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Let's think step by step\""},{"type":"text","text":" to your prompt. This was introduced by Kojima et al. (2022) and is surprisingly effective without any examples."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"User: \"A bakery sells 15 chocolate cookies, 20 vanilla cookies, and 10 almond cookies per day. How many cookies do they sell in 5 days?\"\n\nAssistant: \"Let's think step by step:\n1. Total cookies per day: 15 + 20 + 10 = 45\n2. For 5 days: 45 × 5 = 225\n\nAnswer: 225 cookies\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- When you don't have examples to provide\n- Quick, simple prompts\n- Baseline CoT without setup"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Simple and fast to implement\n- Effective even without examples\n- Particularly useful where you don't have too many examples"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"B. Few-Shot Basic CoT"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Provide "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"few-shot demonstrations"},{"type":"text","text":" showing the reasoning pattern. You include examples in your prompt of how reasoning steps should look."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Question: \"Jenny has 6 oranges. Jaime has 2 fewer oranges than Jenny. How many does Jaime have?\"\n\nReasoning:\n1. Jenny has 6 oranges.\n2. Jaime has 2 fewer than Jenny.\n3. 6 - 2 = 4.\n\nAnswer: 4\n\n---\n\nQuestion: \"Tom has 10 apples. He gives 3 to Sarah and buys 5 more. How many does he have now?\"\n\nReasoning:\n1. Tom starts with 10 apples.\n2. He gives 3 to Sarah: 10 - 3 = 7.\n3. He buys 5 more: 7 + 5 = 12.\n\nAnswer: 12\n\n---\n\nQuestion: \"Maria has 8 books. She loses 2 and buys 4 more. How many does she have?\"\n\nReasoning:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When to use:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- Complex tasks requiring specific reasoning patterns\n- When you can provide examples\n- More control than zero-shot"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- More powerful than zero-shot\n- Model learns the pattern from examples\n- Better for complex reasoning tasks"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. Guided CoT (Template-Based)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Guided CoT"},{"type":"text","text":" provides "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"explicit templates or step-by-step instructions"},{"type":"text","text":" that the model must follow. Instead of letting the model choose how to reason, you define the reasoning structure."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Characteristics"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Guided CoT"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structure"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You define the steps (e.g., \"Step 1: Analyze, Step 2: Plan, Step 3: Execute\")"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flexibility"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low - model must follow your template"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Control"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High - you control the reasoning flow"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Complexity"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium - requires more setup"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How it works:"},{"type":"text","text":" You instruct the model to perform the task step-by-step and output the result of each step."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Guided CoT with Explicit Steps"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Instruction-based:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instructions: Compare the pros and cons of EVs and petroleum-fueled vehicles.\nBreak the task into steps, and output the result of each step as you perform it."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example-based:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Differences between EVs and petroleum-fueled vehicles:\n-\n\nDifferences ordered according to overall impact, highest-impact first:\n1.\n\nSummary of vehicle type differences as pros and cons:\nPros of EVs\n1.\nPros of petroleum-fueled vehicles\n1."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Guided CoT for Debugging"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Debug this code using the following steps:\n\nStep 1: Identify the bug\n- What does the code do wrong?\n- Where is the error occurring?\n\nStep 2: Analyze the root cause\n- What's causing the bug?\n- Is it a logic error, syntax error, or runtime error?\n\nStep 3: Propose a fix\n- What change will fix the bug?\n- Why will this fix work?\n\nStep 4: Show the corrected code\n- Provide the fixed code with comments explaining the change\n\nStep 5: Verify the fix\n- How do you know this will work?\n- What test cases would confirm the fix?\n\nNow debug this code:\n[paste code here]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example: Guided CoT for Decision-Making"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Make a decision about this problem using the following framework:\n\nStep 1: Define the problem clearly\n- What decision needs to be made?\n- What are the constraints?\n\nStep 2: Identify all options\n- List at least 3 possible approaches\n- Don't evaluate yet, just identify\n\nStep 3: Evaluate each option\n- Pros of each option\n- Cons of each option\n- Risks of each option\n\nStep 4: Compare options\n- Which has the most pros?\n- Which has the least risks?\n- Which aligns best with goals?\n\nStep 5: Make the decision\n- State your final choice\n- Explain why this is the best option\n\nProblem: [describe problem]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. Structured CoT (SCoT)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured Chain-of-Thought (SCoT)"},{"type":"text","text":" is the most rigorous approach. It "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"explicitly constrains the model to think using specific structures"},{"type":"text","text":" (e.g., program structures for code, tables for data, XML tags for organization)."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key Paper: Structured CoT for Code Generation"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Research finding:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"In this paper, we propose Structured CoTs (SCoTs) and present a novel prompting technique for code generation, named SCoT prompting. Our motivation is source code contains rich structural information and any code can be composed of three program structures (i.e., sequence, branch, and loop structures). Intuitively, structured intermediate reasoning steps make for structured source code.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Results:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"Compared to CoT prompting, SCoT prompting explicitly constrains LLMs to think about how to solve requirements from the view of source code and further the performance of LLMs in code generation. SCoT prompting outperforms the state-of-the-art baseline - CoT prompting by up to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"13.79% in Pass@1"},{"type":"text","text":".\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Types of Structured CoT"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"A. Program Structure CoT (for Code)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ask the model to use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"program structures"},{"type":"text","text":" (sequence, branch, loop) to build CoTs:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use program structures to build your reasoning:\n\nStep 1: SEQUENCE (linear steps)\n- What operations happen in order?\n- List them sequentially\n\nStep 2: BRANCH (conditional logic)\n- What conditions need to be checked?\n- What happens for each branch?\n\nStep 3: LOOP (repetition)\n- What needs to repeat?\n- What's the loop condition?\n- What happens each iteration?\n\nNow generate code for: [task description]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"B. Tabular CoT (for Data)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tables"},{"type":"text","text":" to organize reasoning steps:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Organize your reasoning in a table:\n\n| Step | Action | Input | Output | Notes |\n|------|--------|-------|--------|-------|\n| 1    |        |       |        |       |\n| 2    |        |       |        |       |\n| 3    |        |       |        |       |\n\nNow solve: [data analysis task]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"C. XML Tag CoT (for Claude)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"XML tags"},{"type":"text","text":" to structure reasoning:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<thinking>\nStep 1: Identify the problem\nStep 2: Break down into sub-steps\nStep 3: Solve each step\nStep 4: Verify the answer\n</thinking>\n\n<answer>\nFinal answer here\n</answer>"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":4},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"D. Template-Based CoT (Universal)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use rigid templates for specific domains:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Follow this exact template for mathematical proofs:\n\n[Problem Statement]\n[Given]\n[To Prove]\n[Proof Steps]\n1. \n2. \n3. \n[Conclusion]\n[Q.E.D.]\n\nProve: [mathematical statement]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Structured CoT Benefits"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Higher accuracy"},{"type":"text","text":" — Outperforms basic CoT by 13.79% in code generation"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Human preference"},{"type":"text","text":" — Developers prefer programs from SCoT"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Robust to examples"},{"type":"text","text":" — Achieves substantial improvements regardless of example quality"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Explicit constraints"},{"type":"text","text":" — Forces model to think about requirements from specific viewpoints"}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Comparison Table"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Aspect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Basic CoT"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Guided CoT"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Structured CoT"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Setup"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple (\"think step by step\")"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium (define steps)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex (rigid templates)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Control"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low (model chooses structure)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium (you define steps)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High (rigid constraints)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Accuracy"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Baseline"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Better than basic"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best (+13.79% for code)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Flexibility"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Medium"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Low"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Simple tasks, quick prompts"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex reasoning, debugging"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Code generation, data analysis"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples needed"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0 (zero-shot) or few"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Few"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Can work with few or many"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to Use Each Approach"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Basic CoT When:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Quick, simple reasoning tasks"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No examples available (zero-shot)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You want minimal setup"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"General-purpose reasoning"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Let's think step by step:Calculate the total cost: 3 items at $15 each, 2 items at $20 each, plus 10% tax.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Guided CoT When:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Complex multi-step tasks (debugging, planning)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You want to control the reasoning flow"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Need transparent, auditable steps"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Decision-making with frameworks"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Break this debugging task into these steps:\n1. Identify the bug\n2. Analyze the root cause\n3. Propose a fix\n4. Show corrected code\n5. Verify the fix\n\nNow debug: [code]\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"✅ "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Structured CoT When:"}]},{"type":"bulletList","content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Code generation (SCoT outperforms CoT by 13.79%)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Data analysis (use tables)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Formal proofs (rigid templates)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"When accuracy is critical"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"Use program structures to build your reasoning:\nStep 1: SEQUENCE — what operations happen in order?\nStep 2: BRANCH — what conditions need checking?\nStep 3: LOOP — what needs to repeat?\n\nNow generate code for: [task]\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Three CoT Approaches:"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Basic CoT"},{"type":"text","text":" — Simplest form:"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero-Shot"},{"type":"text","text":": Just add \"Let's think step by step\" - "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Few-Shot"},{"type":"text","text":": Provide examples showing reasoning pattern - "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"},{"type":"text","text":": Quick, simple tasks"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Guided CoT"},{"type":"text","text":" — Template-based:"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Define explicit steps (e.g., \"Step 1: Analyze, Step 2: Plan...\") - Model must follow your template - "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"},{"type":"text","text":": Debugging, planning, decision-making"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured CoT (SCoT)"},{"type":"text","text":" — Most rigorous:"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Use specific structures (program structures, tables, XML tags) - Explicitly constrains thinking viewpoint - "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best for"},{"type":"text","text":": Code generation (+13.79% accuracy), data analysis, formal proofs"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight:"},{"type":"text","text":" The more structure you provide, the more control and accuracy you get, but the more setup is required. Choose based on your task complexity and accuracy requirements."}]}]}}
